## Step 7: Test strategy summary

The three test files cover distinctly different concerns:

**`field-type-mapper.test.ts`** — pure function, fast, exhaustive. Covers every branch of `mapScalarType` (9 known scalar types + default), both `object` and `enum` kinds, `unsupported` kind, and `isList` wrapping. These tests can run without any file I/O.

**`types-file.test.ts`** — integration of the field filter logic and string generation. Key assertions:
- Enum type unions render correctly
- Model interface includes all fields including relation fields
- `CreateInput` applies the exclusion filter correctly (isId excluded, hasDefaultValue makes required fields optional)
- `UpdateInput` makes all fields optional
- String output is checked with `toContain` (not exact match) for resilience against whitespace changes

**`client-file.test.ts`** — tests URL routing, id type inference, method signatures, and the top-level `RestApiClient` composition. Specific edge cases:
- `mappings.plural` is used when present
- Fallback URL segment when mapping is missing
- Fallback id type (`number | string`) when no `@id` field is present
- `lcFirst` transformation for property names on `RestApiClient`

No mocking of `fs` is required — tests call the pure string-generation functions directly without writing to disk.

